title: New project wizard
body:
Adding basic new project wizard.

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9561483/167773799-e102a9de-d036-4a7f-9c75-04fa30541f87.mp4

### Design
The algorithm selection is using buttons because I expect us to add hyperparameters to each of them, and I think it would be easier to add details into those than if we used a checkbox list.

### TODOs
1. Add a data explorer & SQL editor to be able to create views without connecting with `psql`.
2. Create a snapshot prior to training and show the snapshot analysis before picking algorithms.
3. Replace the cheesy loader with a progress bar indicating which algorithm is currently being trained.
4. For large datasets or high latency data sources, create a snapshot creation progress indicator.
5. Graceful error handling.

title: A few fixes and adding DRF
body:
1. Fix migrations by ~adding `public` to search path~ explicitly using `pgml` schema for for Django tables.
2. Remove unused property `y_column_type` from `Snapshot`.
3. Added Django Rest Framework under `/api` in read-only mode. This helps if we want to fetch things dynamically via XHR, and also to understand what data we have in the database. It's available at https://localhost:8000/api.
4. Remove unnecessary `__init__.py` in `pgml-admin/` folder.
5. Rename `Contributing.md` to `CONTRIBUTING.md`.
6. Refactor `.sort()` to `sorted()`.
